festival.introText:
The UK’s biggest metropolitan festival returned in 2022 to its usual June weekend to kick off the summer festival season. Tyler, The Creator made his long awaited UK headline debut, alongside the iconic 50 Cent who headed to Heaton Park for a UK festival exclusive. The lineup continued with the game changing Megan Thee Stallion and chart topping Lewis Capaldi. Bicep headlined The Valley for the very first time with their much lauded live show. Also not to be missed was the live return of Chase & Status, who brought their largest festival show yet to summer 2022.

Other stellar artists who came to Manchester for live performances at Parklife 2022 included the likes of Loyle Carner, Jamie xx, Arlo Parks, Folamour (Live), Headie One, Central Cee, Fred Again.. ArrDee, Caroline Polachek, Tom Misch and PinkPantheress. DJ sets across the weekend came from the likes of Four Tet, Eric Prydz, Peggy Gou, Carl Cox, Marco Carola , Camelphat, The Blessed Madonna, Andy C, DJ EZ, Sonny Fodera Annie Mac, Jayda G, Mall Grab, Ricardo Villalobos and so many more. It all came together as a very special class of '22.

Parklife also welcomed some brand new stage partners to Heaton Park for the first time, including the likes of Defected, underground giants Fuse, techno heavyweights XXL and tastemakers Eat Your Own Ears and Repercussion. BBC Radio 1Xtra also returned bringing listeners all the action from this year’s festival and, new for 2022, BBC Radio 1 was on hand with special sets being broadcast across the station’s Dance shows. With the Parklife team promising some spectacular new stages to be unveiled over the next few months and this huge array of talent already in place, Parklife 2023 looks pretty unmissable.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer:
Parklife provides a 2:1 ticket scheme for individuals who would be unable to attend their events without bringing a personal assistant. Once you have brought a full price ticket, complete the online access requirement form here: https://form.jotform.com/220164592510347, or download the form, and provide them with Registered Documentation in order to receive your personal assistant ticket. All access requests need to be in by Friday 13th May 2023. 

 

 If you require further information please visit www.parklife.uk.com or e-mail info@parklife.uk.com

faqs.question: When is Parklife 2023?
faqs.answer: Parklife returns to Heaton Park Saturday June 10th & Sunday June 11th 2023.

faqs.question: What is included in a VIP ticket?
faqs.answer:
A VIP ticket includes:

  • VIP fast track entry
  • Luxury toilets
  • VIP area
  • Multiple VIP bars and cocktail bars
  • VIP chill out area
  • Parklife VIP street food fair

faqs.question: Where is Parklife?
faqs.answer: Parklife is located in Heaton park which is around 5 miles north of Manchester city centre. It takes about 20 minutes from the city centre by bus, Metrolink or car. The postcode is M25 2SW.

faqs.question: When does Parklife open / close?
faqs.answer:
Saturday 10th June 2023: 10:30 - 23:00

Sunday 11th June 2023: 11:30 - 23:00

 

Last entry is at 17:00

 

No re-admittance is allowed after leaving the festival site.

faqs.question: Does Parklife have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes, you must be 17 or over to attend Parklife. 17-year-olds will need to be accompanied by an adult (18 or over). There is a max of four 17-year-olds to one adult. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Parklife?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Parklife.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of Parklife 2019
reviewsDisplayFour.body: Rain never stops the immense party in Heaton Park, From Saturdays Headliners Mark Ronson replacing a sorry excuse from Cardi B, Christine And The Queens, The Irrepressible Dave and The King of The Hangar Eric Prydz to Sundays Headliners George Ezra, The Streets, Solange and Blossoms you dance , drink and enjoy every second of this great get together . If you have never experienced a festival before this is the best one for any novice.
